  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2732",
  "title": "HitsPerPageSelector, when selecting the empty value, it sends `undefined` to Algolia",
  "body": "**bug**\r\n\r\nWhen using HitsPerPageSelector with no default value, an empty entry is generated. When selecting any non empty value, and then selecting a value, we get an error from the API: \r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-02-12 at 09 32 52\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/393765/36088470-b9d99bbe-0fd7-11e8-969c-5f60cc3fcd65.png\">\r\n\r\nReproducible here: https://codesandbox.io/s/8qo2m8n89\r\n\r\n**Correct behavior**\r\n\r\nWhen selecting back the empty value, it should remove the hitsPerPage from the searchParameters.\r\n\r\n**Fix**\r\n\r\nMake `refine` accept `\"undefined\"` or `\"\"` on top of the currently handled `undefined` (in the UI, we'll have strings, it's better if we don't have to convert). When the function receives those values, it should unset the parameter.",
